author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: Southern Europe
servings: 2
---

Drop @Cream Cheese{2%tbsp} in a glass of warm water to soften. Wash and dry produce.

Thinly slice @Tomato{1} into rounds. Thinly slice @Fresh Mozzarella{4%oz} into rounds.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together cream cheese and @Pesto{4%tbsp}.

Arrange half the @Sourdough Bread{4%slice} slices on a clean work surface. Spread with creamy pesto. Layer with tomato and mozzarella; season with @Pepper{}. Close sandwiches.

Melt 1 TBSP @Butter{2%tbsp} in a #large, preferably nonstick pan{} over medium heat. Add sandwiches and push around in pan until butter has absorbed. Cook until bread is golden brown and cheese slightly melts, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add another 1 TBSP butter to pan, then flip sandwiches and push around again until butter has absorbed. Cook until bread is golden brown and cheese fully melts, ~{4-6%minutes} more.

> If you have a heavy-bottomed pan, place on top of the sandwiches as they cook for a real panini experience!

While sandwiches toast, in a second small bowl, combine half the @Red Wine Vinegar{5%tsp}, half the @Dijon Mustard{2%tsp}, 2 TBSP @Olive Oil{2%tbsp}, @Sugar{1/4%tsp}, a pinch of @Salt{}, and pepper. Whisk to combine.

> For 4 servings, use all the vinegar, all the mustard, 4 TBSP oil, and 1/2 tsp sugar.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @Arugula{2%oz} with as much vinaigrette as you like.

Halve panini on a diagonal. Divide between plates and serve with salad on the side.